716660f-a.folder: Beekman Street & William Street, Manhattan, NY
716660f-a.text:
(1)
Beekman Street, west from No. 23 (left) a point midway between William and Nassau Streets to Park Row, showing at the latter point a portion of the old United States Post Office, in the southern end of City Hall Park. Overtowering same is the Woolworth Building.
April 19, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same.
January 20, 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
